Noto Serif Ethiopic Md Regular (NotoSerifEthiopic-Medium.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'NotoSerifEthiopic-Medium', Everything looks good.

Pass

Noto Serif Ethiopic Md Regular (NotoSerifEthiopic-Medium.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

(NID 16 + 'Space' + NID 17) 'Noto Serif Ethiopic Medium' ≠ 'Noto Serif Ethiopic Md' (NID 1).

Pass

Noto Serif Ethiopic Bold (NotoSerifEthiopic-Bold.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'NotoSerifEthiopic-Bold', Everything looks good.

Noto Serif Ethiopic Bk Regular (NotoSerifEthiopic-Black.ttf)

name

MS NID 6

MS NID 6, PostScript Name check for illegal characters.
Monotype uses NID 6 for creating CSS classes for their demo HTML. The following characters cause issues in the CSS code: '
, , , &, _, [, ], (, ), {, }, <, >, /, \, %'

NID 6 is 'NotoSerifEthiopic-Black', Everything looks good.

Noto Serif Ethiopic Bk Regular (NotoSerifEthiopic-Black.ttf)

name

MS NID 16/17

MS NID 16 + NID 17 should match NID 1 (+2).
Otherwise cross platform compatibility does not work between Mac (uses NID 16+17) and Windows (uses NID 1+2). (Jan 2019)

(NID 16 + 'Space' + NID 17) 'Noto Serif Ethiopic Black' ≠ 'Noto Serif Ethiopic Bk' (NID 1).
